 <sect1 id="release-7-4-30">
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Release 7.4.30</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>版本 7.4.30</title>

  <formalpara>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Release date:</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>发布日期:</title>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <para>2010-10-04</para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <para>2010-10-04</para>
  </formalpara>


<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   This release contains a variety of fixes from 7.4.29.
   For information about new features in the 7.4 major release, see
   <xref linkend="release-7-4">.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个版本包含各种自7.4.29以来的修复。要想获得关于7.4主版本的新特性信息，
请参阅<xref linkend="release-7-4">。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   This is expected to be the last <productname>PostgreSQL</> release
   in the 7.4.X series.  Users are encouraged to update to a newer
   release branch soon.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这预计是<productname>PostgreSQL</> 7.4.X系列的最后一个版本。
推荐用户尽快更新到新版本。
</para>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Migration to Version 7.4.30</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>迁移到版本 7.4.30</title>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
    A dump/restore is not required for those running 7.4.X.
    However, if you are upgrading from a version earlier than 7.4.26,
    see <xref linkend="release-7-4-26">.
   </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
运行7.4.X的用户不需要转储/恢复。不过，如果您是从一个早于7.4.26的版本升级而来，
那么请参考<xref linkend="release-7-4-26">。
</para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Changes</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>修改列表</title>

   <itemizedlist>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Use a separate interpreter for each calling SQL userid in PL/Perl and
      PL/Tcl (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
为每个在PL/Perl和PL/Tcl中调用的SQL userid使用一个单独的解释器 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This change prevents security problems that can be caused by subverting
      Perl or Tcl code that will be executed later in the same session under
      another SQL user identity (for example, within a <literal>SECURITY
      DEFINER</> function).  Most scripting languages offer numerous ways that
      that might be done, such as redefining standard functions or operators
      called by the target function.  Without this change, any SQL user with
      Perl or Tcl language usage rights can do essentially anything with the
      SQL privileges of the target function's owner.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个修改阻止可以由破坏稍后在同一个会话中另一个SQL用户身份执行的Perl或Tcl代码引起的安全问题
（例如，在一个<literal>SECURITY DEFINER</>函数中）。大多数脚本语言提供多种可能执行的方式，
比如重定义被目标函数调用的标准函数或操作符。没有这个修改，
任意拥有Perl或Tcl语言使用权限的SQL用户本质上都可以用目标函数的所有者的SQL权限做任何事情。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      The cost of this change is that intentional communication among Perl
      and Tcl functions becomes more difficult.  To provide an escape hatch,
      PL/PerlU and PL/TclU functions continue to use only one interpreter
      per session.  This is not considered a security issue since all such
      functions execute at the trust level of a database superuser already.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个修改的成本是Perl和Tcl函数之间有意的交流变得更加困难。为了提供一个安全舱口，
PL/PerlU和PL/TclU函数继续每个会话只使用有一个解释器。这不认为是一个安全问题，
因为所有这样的函数都早已在数据库超级用户的信任级别执行了。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      It is likely that third-party procedural languages that claim to offer
      trusted execution have similar security issues.  We advise contacting
      the authors of any PL you are depending on for security-critical
      purposes.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
有可能要求提供受信任的执行的第三方的过程语言有相似的安全问题。
我们建议为了关键性的安全目的，联系任何你依赖的PL的作者。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Our thanks to Tim Bunce for pointing out this issue (CVE-2010-3433).
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
感谢Tim Bunce指出这个问题 (CVE-2010-3433)。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Prevent possible crashes in <function>pg_get_expr()</> by disallowing
      it from being called with an argument that is not one of the system
      catalog columns it's intended to be used with
      (Heikki Linnakangas, Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
阻止<function>pg_get_expr()</>中可能的崩溃，通过不允许它被调用，
有一个争论是它尝试使用多个系统目录字段 (Heikki Linnakangas, Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix <quote>cannot handle unplanned sub-select</quote> error (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复<quote>cannot handle unplanned sub-select</quote>错误 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This occurred when a sub-select contains a join alias reference that
      expands into an expression containing another sub-select.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
当一个子查询包含一个连接别名引用扩大为一个表达式包含另一个子查询时会发生这个错误。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Take care to fsync the contents of lockfiles (both
      <filename>postmaster.pid</> and the socket lockfile) while writing them
      (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
在写锁文件（包括<filename>postmaster.pid</>和套接字锁文件）时要小心的同步锁文件的内容 (Tom Lane)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This omission could result in corrupted lockfile contents if the
      machine crashes shortly after postmaster start.  That could in turn
      prevent subsequent attempts to start the postmaster from succeeding,
      until the lockfile is manually removed.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
如果机器在主进程启动后很快就崩溃了，那么这个疏忽会导致锁文件内容损坏。
这会阻止随后启动主进程的尝试成功，直到手动的移除锁文件。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Improve <filename>contrib/dblink</>'s handling of tables containing
      dropped columns (Tom Lane)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
改善<filename>contrib/dblink</>处理含有删除的字段的表 (Tom Lane)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix connection leak after <quote>duplicate connection name</quote>
      errors in <filename>contrib/dblink</> (Itagaki Takahiro)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复<filename>contrib/dblink</>中出现<quote>duplicate connection name</quote>
错误之后的连接漏洞 (Itagaki Takahiro)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Update build infrastructure and documentation to reflect the source code
      repository's move from CVS to Git (Magnus Hagander and others)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
更新基础构造和文档，以反应源代码从CVS迁移到了Git (Magnus Hagander and others)
</para>
    </listitem>

   </itemizedlist>

  </sect2>
 </sect1>

 <sect1 id="release-7-4-29">
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Release 7.4.29</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>版本 7.4.29</title>

  <formalpara>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Release date:</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>发布日期：</title>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <para>2010-05-17</para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <para>2010-05-17</para>
  </formalpara>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   This release contains a variety of fixes from 7.4.28.
   For information about new features in the 7.4 major release, see
   <xref linkend="release-7-4">.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个版本包含各种自7.4.28以来的修复。关于7.4主版本的新特性信息，
请参阅<xref linkend="release-7-4">。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   The <productname>PostgreSQL</> community will stop releasing updates
   for the 7.4.X release series in July 2010.
   Users are encouraged to update to a newer release branch soon.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
<productname>PostgreSQL</>社区将在2010年7月份停止对7.4.X版本系列的更新。
建议用户尽快更新到最新的版本。
</para>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Migration to Version 7.4.29</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>迁移到版本 7.4.29</title>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
    A dump/restore is not required for those running 7.4.X.
    However, if you are upgrading from a version earlier than 7.4.26,
    see <xref linkend="release-7-4-26">.
   </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
运行7.4.X的版本不需要转储/恢复。不过，如果你是从一个早于7.4.26的版本升级而来，
那么请参阅<xref linkend="release-7-4-26">。
</para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Changes</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>修改列表</title>

   <itemizedlist>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Enforce restrictions in <literal>plperl</> using an opmask applied to
      the whole interpreter, instead of using <filename>Safe.pm</>
      (Tim Bunce, Andrew Dunstan)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
使用一个opmask应用到整个解释器，执行<literal>plperl</>中的限制条件，
而不是使用<filename>Safe.pm</> (Tim Bunce, Andrew Dunstan)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Recent developments have convinced us that <filename>Safe.pm</> is too
      insecure to rely on for making <literal>plperl</> trustable.  This
      change removes use of <filename>Safe.pm</> altogether, in favor of using
      a separate interpreter with an opcode mask that is always applied.
      Pleasant side effects of the change include that it is now possible to
      use Perl's <literal>strict</> pragma in a natural way in
      <literal>plperl</>, and that Perl's <literal>$a</> and <literal>$b</>
      variables work as expected in sort routines, and that function
      compilation is significantly faster.  (CVE-2010-1169)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
最近的发展使我们相信<filename>Safe.pm</>太不安全了，不能依赖它来使得
<literal>plperl</>可以信赖。这个修改完全删除了<filename>Safe.pm</>的使用，
支持总是使用一个单独的带有操作码的解释器。这个修改令人愉快的副作用包括：
现在在<literal>plperl</>中以自然的方式使用Perl的<literal>strict</>编译指示是可能的了，
Perl的<literal>$a</>和<literal>$b</>变量在排序例程中像预期的那样工作了，
并且函数编译更快了。 (CVE-2010-1169)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Prevent PL/Tcl from executing untrustworthy code from
      <structname>pltcl_modules</> (Tom)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
阻止PL/Tcl执行<structname>pltcl_modules</>中不可靠的代码 (Tom)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      PL/Tcl's feature for autoloading Tcl code from a database table
      could be exploited for trojan-horse attacks, because there was no
      restriction on who could create or insert into that table.  This change
      disables the feature unless <structname>pltcl_modules</> is owned by a
      superuser.  (However, the permissions on the table are not checked, so
      installations that really need a less-than-secure modules table can
      still grant suitable privileges to trusted non-superusers.)  Also,
      prevent loading code into the unrestricted <quote>normal</> Tcl
      interpreter unless we are really going to execute a <literal>pltclu</>
      function.  (CVE-2010-1170)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
PL/Tcl自动从数据库表中加载Tcl代码的特性可能会被特洛伊木马攻击利用，
因为没有谁可以创建或插入到那个表的限制。这个修改使该特性失效，
除非<structname>pltcl_modules</>属于超级用户。（不过，在表上的权限是不检查的，
所以实际上需要较少安全模块的表的安装仍然可以赋予合适的权限给受信任的非超级用户。）
还有，阻止加载代码到不受限制的<quote>正常</>Tcl解释器，
除非我们真正要执行一个<literal>pltclu</>函数。 (CVE-2010-1170)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Do not allow an unprivileged user to reset superuser-only parameter
      settings (Alvaro)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
不允许非特权的用户重置超级用户仅有的参数设置 (Alvaro)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Previously, if an unprivileged user ran <literal>ALTER USER ... RESET
      ALL</> for himself, or <literal>ALTER DATABASE ... RESET ALL</> for
      a database he owns, this would remove all special parameter settings
      for the user or database, even ones that are only supposed to be
      changeable by a superuser.  Now, the <command>ALTER</> will only
      remove the parameters that the user has permission to change.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
以前，如果一个非特权用户为他自己运行<literal>ALTER USER ... RESET ALL</>，
或者为他拥有的一个数据库运行<literal>ALTER DATABASE ... RESET ALL</>，
都将为该用户或数据库删除所有的特殊参数设置，即使其中有只支持超级用户可以修改的设置。
现在，<command>ALTER</>将只删除用户有权限修改的参数。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Avoid possible crash during backend shutdown if shutdown occurs
      when a <literal>CONTEXT</> addition would be made to log entries (Tom)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
如果关闭发生在<literal>CONTEXT</>添加来记录条目时，避免后端关闭期间可能的崩溃 (Tom)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      In some cases the context-printing function would fail because the
      current transaction had already been rolled back when it came time
      to print a log message.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
在某些情况下，上下文打印功能可能会失败，因为当它要打印一个日志信息时，
当前的事务早已回滚了。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Update PL/Perl's <filename>ppport.h</> for modern Perl versions
      (Andrew)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
为现在的Perl版本更新PL/Perl的<filename>ppport.h</> (Andrew)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix assorted memory leaks in PL/Python (Andreas Freund, Tom)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复PL/Python中的各种内存泄露 (Andreas Freund, Tom)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Ensure that <filename>contrib/pgstattuple</> functions respond to cancel
      interrupts promptly (Tatsuhito Kasahara)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
确保<filename>contrib/pgstattuple</>函数响应迅速的取消中断 (Tatsuhito Kasahara)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Make server startup deal properly with the case that
      <function>shmget()</> returns <literal>EINVAL</> for an existing
      shared memory segment (Tom)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
使服务器启动适当的处理<function>shmget()</>为一个已经存在的共享内存段返回
<literal>EINVAL</>的情况 (Tom)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This behavior has been observed on BSD-derived kernels including macOS.
      It resulted in an entirely-misleading startup failure complaining that
      the shared memory request size was too large.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个行为已经在BSD衍生的核心程序包括macOS上观察到。它导致一个完全误导的启动失败，
抱怨共享内存请求大小太大。
</para>
    </listitem>

   </itemizedlist>

  </sect2>
 </sect1>

 <sect1 id="release-7-4-28">
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Release 7.4.28</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>版本 7.4.28</title>

  <formalpara>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <title>Release date:</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <title>发布日期：</title>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
  <para>2010-03-15</para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
  <para>2010-03-15</para>
  </formalpara>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   This release contains a variety of fixes from 7.4.27.
   For information about new features in the 7.4 major release, see
   <xref linkend="release-7-4">.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这个版本包括各种自7.4.27以来的修复。关于7.4主版本的新特性的信息，
请参阅<xref linkend="release-7-4">。
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
   The <productname>PostgreSQL</> community will stop releasing updates
   for the 7.4.X release series in July 2010.
   Users are encouraged to update to a newer release branch soon.
  </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
<productname>PostgreSQL</>社区将在2010年7月份停止对7.4.X版本系列的更新。
建议用户尽快更新到最新的版本。
</para>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Migration to Version 7.4.28</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>迁移到版本 7.4.28</title>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
    A dump/restore is not required for those running 7.4.X.
    However, if you are upgrading from a version earlier than 7.4.26,
    see <xref linkend="release-7-4-26">.
   </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
运行7.4.X的用户不需要转储/恢复。不过，如果你是从一个早于7.4.26的版本升级而来，
那么请查看<xref linkend="release-7-4-26">。
</para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
   <title>Changes</title>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
   <title>修改列表</title>

   <itemizedlist>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Add new configuration parameter <varname>ssl_renegotiation_limit</> to
      control how often we do session key renegotiation for an SSL connection
      (Magnus)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
添加新的配置参数<varname>ssl_renegotiation_limit</>，
控制多长时间为SSL连接做一次会话秘钥重新协商 (Magnus)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This can be set to zero to disable renegotiation completely, which may
      be required if a broken SSL library is used.  In particular, some
      vendors are shipping stopgap patches for CVE-2009-3555 that cause
      renegotiation attempts to fail.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
可以设置为0来完全禁用重新协商，如果使用了破损的SSL库可能会需要这个。
特别的，一些供应商提供暂时的CVE-2009-3555的补丁导致重新协商的尝试失败。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Make <function>substring()</> for <type>bit</> types treat any negative
      length as meaning <quote>all the rest of the string</> (Tom)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
使得<function>substring()</>的<type>bit</>类型对待负的长度为意味着
<quote>所有剩余的字符串</> (Tom)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      The previous coding treated only -1 that way, and would produce an
      invalid result value for other negative values, possibly leading to
      a crash (CVE-2010-0442).
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
以前的代码只对待-1为这种方式，并且会为其它负值生成一个无效的结果值，
有可能会导致崩溃 (CVE-2010-0442)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      Fix some cases of pathologically slow regular expression matching (Tom)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
修复一些正则表达式匹配变慢的情况 (Tom)
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      When reading <filename>pg_hba.conf</> and related files, do not treat
      <literal>@something</> as a file inclusion request if the <literal>@</>
      appears inside quote marks; also, never treat <literal>@</> by itself
      as a file inclusion request (Tom)
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
当读取<filename>pg_hba.conf</>和相关的文件时，如果<literal>@</>出现在双引号标记的内部，
那么不要将<literal>@something</>当做文件包含查询；还有，
永远不要将<literal>@</>本身当做文件包含查询 (Tom)
</para>

<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
<para>
      This prevents erratic behavior if a role or database name starts with
      <literal>@</>.  If you need to include a file whose path name
      contains spaces, you can still do so, but you must write
      <literal>@"/path to/file"</> rather than putting the quotes around
      the whole construct.
     </para>
____________________________________________________________________________-->
<para>
这阻止了当用户或者数据库名字以<literal>@</>开始时的不规律行为。
如果你需要包括一个文件的整个路径名（包括空格），你仍然可以这样做，
但是必须写<literal>@"/path to/file"</>而不是使双引号包含整个构造。
</para>
    </listitem>

    <listitem>
<!--==========================orignal english content==========================
